      "type": "uofa:EvidenceNode",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modeling studies supporting power-law coefficient selection",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior experimental and computational hemolysis studies (Giersiepen 1990, Zhang 2011, Taskin 2012, Goubergrits 2016) establishing the basis for power-law hemolysis model parameter selection. This node consolidates evidence from over two decades of blood trauma research, including capillary tube experiments, Couette flow data, and CFD validation campaigns across multiple pump geometries. The synthesis informed turbulence model selection, hemolysis scalar transport formulation, and acceptable RH threshold calibration for the current COU."
